\multicolumn{1}{!{\color[HTML]{000000}\vrule width 1pt}>{\raggedright}p{\dimexpr 2in+0\tabcolsep}}{\textcolor[HTML]{000000}{\fontsize{10}{10}\selectfont{Double\ Empathy}}} & \multicolumn{1}{!{\color[HTML]{000000}\vrule width 1pt}>{\raggedright}p{\dimexpr 4in+0\tabcolsep}!{\color[HTML]{000000}\vrule width 1pt}}{\textcolor[HTML]{000000}{\fontsize{10}{10}\selectfont{Double\ empathy\ refers\ to\ how:}}\textcolor[HTML]{000000}{\fontsize{10}{10}\selectfont{\linebreak }}\textcolor[HTML]{000000}{\fontsize{10}{10}\selectfont{1.\ It\ is\ easier\ to\ understand\ the\ mindset\ of\ people\ who\ are\ similar\ to\ you}}\textcolor[HTML]{000000}{\fontsize{10}{10}\selectfont{\linebreak }}\textcolor[HTML]{000000}{\fontsize{10}{10}\selectfont{2.\ It\ is\ more\ difficult\ to\ understand\ the\ mindset\ of\ those\ who\ are\ different\ from\ you}}\textcolor[HTML]{000000}{\fontsize{10}{10}\selectfont{\linebreak }}\textcolor[HTML]{000000}{\fontsize{10}{10}\selectfont{This\ concept\ was\ specifically\ developed\ by\ the\ autistic\ autism\ researcher\ Damian\ Milton\ to\ explain\ how\ autistics\ and\ neurotypicals\ empathize\ with\ each\ other.\ It\ explains\ how\ allistics\ (non-autistics)\ struggle\ to\ understand\ the\ lived\ experiences\ of\ autistics\ and\ autistics\ struggle\ to\ understand\ the\ lived\ experiences\ of\ allistics.\ Likewise,\ autistics\ are\ better\ at\ understanding\ other\ autistics\ and\ allistics\ are\ better\ at\ understanding\ other\ allistics.\ https://embrace-autism.com/autism-and-the-double-empathy-problem/}}} \\

